-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 				    SPOT
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Keys:

Main title screen-
	S- Start a game
	E- Edit or Change Board
	O- Go to options

At edit board-
	Y- Symmetry on/off
	U- Undo
	E- Exit
	S- Shake

At the option screen-
	E- Exit

At the play board-
	Q- Quit or pause game


How to play:

	The object of this game is to capture all of your opponents squares.
	The game plays much like Othello, but the methods of moving and
	capturing pieces is different.

	If you are the 'X', you may move to any of these adjacent squares:
				
				.....
				.....
				..X..
				.....
				.....

	You may not move on top of another player.  If you move to one of the
	squares directly adjacent to you, your piece will be replicated.  If
	you move to a square on the outer edge of your limits, your piece will
	move, but it will not be replicated.

	To capture opponents game pieces, you move to a square adjacent to the
	piece you wish to capture.  The person with the most pieces when the
	board is full is the winner. 

	There may also be bonus squares in the game.  If you land on one, a
	slot machine type game will come up.  Hit the button to stop each
	column.  If three spots line up, you get a free turn.  If three seven
	up logos line up, you get 7 extra seconds in a timed game.  If three
	cherries line up, you get to move any of your pieces to any free 
	square.  If three virgins line up, you can swap any one of your
	pieces with any one of your opponent's pieces.

  	Thats about it, have fun.
